The Telegraph - Calcutta : Business

 LOOSE CHANGE

 ING Vysya Bank has introduced Freedom Savings Account, a zero balance account for the low and middle income group customers. The account is a personal banking zero balance account. It comes with an international debit card, free unlimited transactions on all ING Vysya Bank ATMs and four free transactions per month on ATMs of other banks with which it has a network sharing arrangement. To access the account through Internet or SMS or mobile banking, customers will have to pay an annual fee of Rs 1,000.

 UTI Mutual Fund plans to launch UTI Lifestyle Fund next month. It is a three-year close-ended diversified equity fund that will invest only in stocks of those companies associated with lifestyle products. The minimum investment will be Rs 5,000. The fund entails a higher risk and aims at young investors who are in a position to hold on to their investment for some time. 

 Birla Sun Life Mutual Fund has announced a maiden dividend of 20 per cent, or Rs 2.00 per unit having a face value of Rs 10. The dividend will be tax free in the hands of investors who have joined the dividend option of the scheme. The record date for the payout has been fixed as June 19.




